History of Slots:
----------------
v2.05   9-10-94 Turns was not being updated correctly, fixed.
                Added AmigaGuide documentation.
                First Public release.

v2.04   8-11-94 Deleted an ending CR during the screen draw, so the screen
                wouldn't scroll up.

v2.03   8-08-94 Made it so you can QUIT during the HOLD phase.
                Changed some inner workings of HiScores().
                Graphical optimizations.
                Added a minimun baud check.  9600 baud or better.

v2.02   8-07-94 Moved the screen down a line, since DLG sysops need the top
                for their status line.
                Changed it so instead of hitting START to enter HOLD mode,
                it automatically goes into HOLD mode, and if you don't HOLD
                any, then it treats it as a new roll.
                Changed it so it automatically goes into HI/LO, user just
                selects QUIT (default) if they don't want to play.

v2.00   7-06-94 It has been almost a year since my last update. :)
                Changed to a keyfile system which is easier for both the user
                and me!
                Changed the registration system, see REGISTERING.
----

v1.50r  8-14-93 New config file so sysop can set the number of days a user
                has to wait before getting a new loan (which has been
                lowered to $5000 instead of the starting amount of $10k).

v1.49r  6-03-93 Changed it so if a new player doesn't gamble any of his
                money by taking a turn, he won't be listed in the high
                score list.
                Fixed problem in the monthly high score list.
                Fixed small display glitch.

v1.47r  5-17-93 Fixed it so that a player now DOES get a new loan after a
                week.  Sorry about that Rich!

v1.46r  5-10-93 Fixed it so Slots now checks for a CTRL-C (Break) everywhere
                not just in the main function.  Problem found by Bill
                Seymour.

v1.45r  5-02-93 Fixed small bug in highscore table that would not delete old
                win/lost records of players with start of new month.
                Added check to make sure win/lost doesn't go over the max
                limit.
                Fixed bug that would cause a GURU (divide by zero) because
                of a small typo.  GURU first experienced by Richard Muller.

v1.44r  4-25-93 Fixed it so that when you win the jackpot, it adds it to
                your total winnings.  Bug found by Richard Muller.

v1.43r  4-21-93 Changed the high score setup as suggested by Richard Muller.

v1.42r  4-20-93 Fixed small graphical errors.
                Fixed bug in high score list.

v1.41r  4-18-93 Fixed it so players get their turns reset.  Thanx to Richard
                Muller for pointing that out.

v1.4r   4-14-93 Changed it so player can only type numbers for bets.
                Improved argument handler.

v1.3    4-14-93 Public release version.
                Corrected The Matrix's phone number, pointed out by
                the sysop, Anthony Fiarito.
                Finished the high score list feature in the registered
                version.
                New winning ratios as requested by Richard Muller.
                Other miscellaneous changes.

v1.2    4-11-93 Added a new argument, [option], in case your BBS software
                doesn't send a '1' or 'on'.
                Added a redraw command, something that is obvious that I
                somehow forgot, pointed out by Richard Muller.

v1.1    4-11-93 Changed the <ANSI> argument to accept either a '1' or 'on'
                since some BBS's use one or the other.  Thanx to Richard
                Muller for pointing this out.

v1.0    4-10-93 Initial release.
